\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi0\ql\rtlch\af5\afs21\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs21\lang2057\i\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i\b0 I vow to liberate all sentient beings}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i\b0 I vow to cut off endless vexations}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i\b0 I vow to master limitless approaches to Dharma}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i\b0 I vow to attain Supreme Buddhahood.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs21\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs21\lang2057\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs21\lang2057\i0\b0 Sometimes we may feel such vows go far beyond human possibility.  Yet we do not enter any quest with the notion of stopping halfway.  The Grail may be far away but there is no hesitation.  A warrior does not enter battle with the notion of partly winning. 
 A farmer does not plant seeds to see the crops half grown.  Whatever the difficulties, the Zen practitioner persists in the courage of the warrior or in the faith of the skilled farmer.  Each vow is a personal question, a 'koan', that lasts a lifetime.  W
hat is it to do thus?}
